### Function to Convert Markdown to HTML in C++ 

**Problem Statement**: 

- Write a C++ function that takes a reference to a `std::string` containing markdown formatted text and returns a `std::string` containing html formatted text.

**Solution**: 

- Use the `boost::spirit::qi` library to parse the markdown text and convert it to HTML.
- Define a grammar for markdown using the `boost::spirit::qi` library.
- Use the `qi::parse` function to parse the markdown text and generate the corresponding HTML.

**Code**: 

```cpp
#include <string>
#include <iostream>
#include <boost/spirit/include/qi.hpp>

namespace qi = boost::spirit::qi;

std::string convertMarkdownToHtml(const std::string& markdown) {
    std::string html;

    // Define a grammar for markdown using the boost::spirit::qi library
    qi::rule<std::string::const_iterator, std::string()> markdownRule =
        "text" >> *(qi::lit("#") >> "text");

    // Use the qi::parse function to parse the markdown text and generate the corresponding HTML
    bool result = qi::parse(markdown.begin(), markdown.end(), markdownRule, html);

    if (!result) {
        std::cerr << "Error: Failed to parse markdown" << std::endl;
        return "";
    }

    return html;
}

int main() {
    std::string markdown = "# This is a heading\n\nThis is some text.";
    std::string html = convertMarkdownToHtml(markdown);
    std::cout << html << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

